Questions
Regarding Equation/Notation $\mathcal{H}(C|I)$ on Page 4, how exactly do you propose to compute this conditional entropy in practice, given that $I$ is informal natural language and $C$ is a high-dimensional property graph?
In Figure 1, you depict a clean, bidirectional synchronization via $\Phi$ and $\Psi$. Given that code generation inherently drops higher-level semantic intent, how do you prevent $\Psi$ from simply hallucinating missing context when attempting to rehydrate $C$ from raw code?
The 'Alternative Views' section on Page 5 claims the overhead of maintaining $C$ is "front-loaded." What specific evidence or historical analogies give you confidence that developers will tolerate this overhead, given the historical failure of synchronized UML and similar Model-Driven Architecture efforts?
Without a results table or empirical benchmark, how should the ICML community validate your claim that the cognitive load of navigating a property graph is lower than reading raw artifact diffs?
